<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861226-0096 </DOCNO><HL> Universal Health AcceptsStock for New Trust Shares</HL><DD> 12/26/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> UHSIBBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> KING OF PRUSSIA, Pa.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Universal Health Services Inc. said it accepted for exchange into new shares of Universal Health Realty Income Trust three million validly tendered Universal Health Services common shares and $75 million face amount of the company's debentures.    The hospital management concern said shares of the trust will begin trading today on the New York Stock Exchange on a when-issued basis.    The shares exchanged represent about 27% of the more than 11 million shares of Universal Health Services common validly tendered. The convertible debentures represent about 90% of the $83.7 million face amount validly tendered. </TEXT></DOC>